A: The problem is that you are closing the PrintWriter after each write. This is causing the data to be flushed immediately, and you are only seeing the last line of data.
Instead, you should close the PrintWriter after all the data has been written. Here's how you can do it:
PrintWriter printWriter = new PrintWriter(socket.getOutputStream(), true);
printWriter.write("1");
printWriter.write("2");
printWriter.write("3");
printWriter.close();

Then, on the receiving side, you can read all lines using a loop:
BufferedReader bufferedReader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(socket.getInputStream()));
String line;
while ((line = bufferedReader.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}

This will print each line of data separately.

